						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar built into the Peddāpuram gate in the Missionary's compound.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1125, Mina, śu, 3, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the gift of land made by some Brāhmaṇas of Koṇadina village for a perpetual lamp and providing offerings to the god Sōmēśvaradēva of Tilatīrtha at Sūryanārāyaṇapuram.</p>						

